OL,3,CHow could the Senedd reform affect you?
OL,5,FThe party's leader, Rhun ap Iorwerth
OL,6,Fsaid that "Plaid Cymru MSs will be
OL,7,Fvoting this week for a stronger, more
OL,8,Fdemocratic and more representative
OL,9,FSenedd which will be better able to
OL,10,Fmake a positive difference to the
OL,11,Flives of people right across our
OL,12,Fcountry.J"The reformed Senedd will be
OL,13,Fbetter equipped to serve the citizens
OL,14,Fof Wales, providing better scrutiny of
OL,15,FWelsh Government policy and spending
OL,16,Fdecisions, and providing a better
OL,17,Ffocus on improving public services.
OL,18,F"Wales should not be democratically
OL,19,Fshortchanged. Once passed, the Senedd
OL,20,FReform Bill will place Welsh democracy
OL,21,Fon firmer foundations and bring us
OL,22,Fcloser to the relative sizes of the
OL,23,Flegislatures in Scotland and Northern
OL,24,FIreland. The health of our democracy
OL,25,Fdepends on it and this stands in stark
OL,26,Fcontrast to the way in which Wales's
